@startuml Fig_3_4_5_Positional_Encoding_Visualization
title Fig 3.4.5: Positional Encoding (as implemented in SLM)\nLearned absolute positions — conceptual "heatmap"

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE

rectangle "**nn.Embedding(block_size, n_embd)**\nlearnable matrix **P** ∈ ℝ^{T_max × d_model}\nrows = position 0 … T_max−1" as EMB

rectangle "For sequence length **T**:\n**pos** = arange(0, T)\n**PE** = P[pos]  // (T, d_model)\nbroadcast + token embeddings" as LOOKUP
EMB --> LOOKUP

rectangle "Visualization idea\n(plot for thesis):\n— X-axis: dimension index **j** ∈ [0, d_model)\n— Y-axis: position **i** ∈ [0, T)\n— Color: P[i, j] after training\n(sinusoidal curves appear only if you\nuse fixed sin/cos PE; here expect\nirregular learned structure)" as VIZ
LOOKUP .. VIZ : export / matplotlib

note as N1
  **Code reference:**\n  **x** = tok_emb(idx) + pos_emb(pos)\n  **block_size** = max context (e.g. 256)\n  This is **not** the fixed sinusoidal\n  Vaswani et al. formula; it matches\n  **GPT-2–style learned** positions.
end note

EMB .. N1

@enduml
